<h1 id="third-party-projects">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#third-party-projects" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Third Party Projects
</h1>

<h3 id="phosh">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#phosh" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Phosh <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/World/Phosh/phosh"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A pure wayland shell for mobile devices.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@agx:sigxcpu.org">Guido</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Matthew Dennis made <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/World/Phosh/phosh">Phosh</a>&rsquo;s bottom bar smaller so there&rsquo;s more space for apps like video players on your phone - especially in landscape. The screenshot features <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/guidog/livi">livi</a> a little video player targeting mobile:

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/12/twig-128/PwGwHuYsPJmLrwHSIIwAbesS.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="graphs">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#graphs" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Graphs <a href="https://graphs.sjoerd.se"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Plot and manipulate data</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@sjoerdb93:matrix.org">Sjoerd Stendahl</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Since the summer we&rsquo;ve been working hard on the next release of Graphs. A full announcement of the next stable release will follow soon, but we want to give it a bit of time to do some more testing and final polish to make sure the next stable release is the best it can be. In the meantime, I&rsquo;m happy to announce an official beta version which is feature-complete, and encourage anyone to give it a spin!</p>
<p>Some of the highlights of this upcoming release include, but are not limited to:</p>
<ul>
<li>A major UI overhaul with the new GNOME 45 widgets</li>
<li>Brand new style previews</li>
<li>Curve fitting</li>
<li>Touchpad gestures are now supported on the canvas to zoom and pan the view.</li>
<li>Translations are now hosted on <a href="https://hosted.weblate.org/projects/graphs/graphs/">Weblate</a>. Click the link if you want to contribute to translations. Currently we&rsquo;re missing strings for Spanish and German, but help with other languages are always welcome as well.</li>
</ul>
<p>To install the beta, follow the instructions on <a href="https://github.com/Sjoerd1993/Graphs/">our Github page</a>. Stay tuned for a full announcement for the stable release somewhere in the upcoming weeks!

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/12/twig-128/sNrFqRMgwJKNGbahWHogiEgh.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/12/twig-128/ajuhBIajgRpnvtklRPdmNgme.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/12/twig-128/wJwDumNCOOxjooCNmHyuoHoM.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="fretboard">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#fretboard" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Fretboard <a href="https://github.com/bragefuglseth/fretboard"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Look up guitar chords</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@bragefuglseth:gnome.org">Brage Fuglseth</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This week I published Fretboard 5.0. It may not arrive in wrapping paper, but this timely release still includes some nice gifts:</p>
<ul>
<li>An enharmonic indicator that lets you see when chords have more than one possible name</li>
<li>Automatic chord name formatting, turning your sloppily typed “bb maj7” into a beautiful “B♭maj7”</li>
<li>More consistent keyboard shortcuts</li>
<li>Enhanced accessibility for screen readers</li>
<li>German and Swedish translations, making Fretboard available in a total of 13 languages</li>
</ul>
<p>If you would like to come with suggestions, report bugs, translate the app, or contribute otherwise, feel free to reach out! Download Fretboard on <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/dev.bragefuglseth.Fretboard">Flathub</a>.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/12/twig-128/7c71d8239d534bacc557b49a46d8647505f1cfce1739090155437817856.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="flare">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#flare" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Flare <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/de.schmidhuberj.Flare"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Chat with your friends on Signal.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@schmiddi:matrix.org">schmiddi</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Version 0.11.0 of Flare got now released. This release brings many important fixes for bugs which made previous versions pretty much unusable for new devices. This includes a fix for syncing contacts, but also a fix for linking recently breaking. This release also includes many UI improvements, like an improved setup window which introduces users to Flare, lets them choose between using Flare as a linked device or as a primary device (this is currently still disabled as it still needs more extensive testing) and gives further information on what important bugs are still in Flare and how to get in contact. There were also many more minor UI improvements and also updates to the newest GTK and libadwaita versions.</p>
<p>You may have noticed that the last release of Flare was quite some time ago (about 4 months). This was due to aforementioned issues we had with contact syncing and linking; those first required upstream fixes and those fixes furthermore introduced some regressions which also needed to be fixed. This required in total eight beta releases for everything to be (hopefully) fixed.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/12/twig-128/cPVBbcHutnKthbPuFpKLDMZD.png" alt="" />

